To fix the `NullPointerException` error related to the `vmbConfig` object being null, you need to ensure that the `vmbConfig` object is properly initialized before calling methods on it within your test case. Here's an updated version of the test case that initializes the `vmbConfig` mock and provides the necessary behavior:

```java
import org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;
import org.mockito.Mock;
import org.mockito.InjectMocks;
import org.mockito.MockitoAnnotations;

import static org.mockito.Mockito.when;

import static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;
import org.junit.jupiter.api.BeforeEach;

public class AlarmReceiverTest {

    @InjectMocks
    private AlarmReceiver alarmReceiver;

    @Mock
    private VMBParams vmbParams;

    @Mock
    private Consumer<byte[]> consumer;

    @Mock
    private VMBConfig vmbConfig;

    @BeforeEach
    void initMocks() {
        MockitoAnnotations.openMocks(this);
    }

    @Test
    void testGetConnection() {
        // Set up the necessary mocks for the test
        when(vmbParams.getConsumerVMBConfig()).thenReturn(vmbConfig);
        when(vmbConfig.getTopic()).thenReturn("testTopic"); // Mock the behavior you expect
        when(VMBUtil.createConsumerConnection(vmbConfig, null)).thenReturn(consumer);

        // Call the method under test
        alarmReceiver.getConnection();

        // Validate the behavior
        assertThat(alarmReceiver.get_consumer()).isEqualTo(consumer);
    }

    // Add more test cases to cover other scenarios in the getConnection() method

}
```

In this updated version, we have annotated the `@InjectMocks` annotation on the `AlarmReceiver` field to let Mockito inject the mocks automatically. The `@BeforeEach` method initializes the mocks using `MockitoAnnotations.openMocks(this)` before each test method is executed.

Ensure that your `AlarmReceiver` class sets up the `vmbConfig` object correctly during its instantiation or through a setter method. This way, the `vmbConfig` mock will not be null when the `getConnection()` method is invoked in the test case.

